observationText: The HS53T cell line was derived from a human malignant peripheral nerve sheath tumor (MPNST) and harbors a heterozygous NF1 mutation (c.2041C>T, p.Arg681Ter).
The HS53T cell line exhibited a homozygous deletion of the CDKN2A tumor suppressor gene.
The HS53T cell line had a highly gained region in chromosome 7 containing the EGFR receptor.
The HS53T cell line exhibited a homozygous deletion of the CDKN2B tumor suppressor gene in addition to CDKN2A.
HS53T cells had a focal amplification of the MDM2 oncogene.
The HS53T cell line exhibited a homozygous deletion of the SUZ12 gene, which is a component of the Polycomb repressive complex 2 (PRC2).
